725469f-a.title: Queens: 56th Avenue - East 56th Street.
725469f-a.text:
Fifty-sixth Ave. (along rear of house), north side, just east
of 56th Street, showing the former summer home of Gov. De Witt
Clinton in a set of three views.
1922.
Views 1 and 2.
View 3: September 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

725478f-a.title: Queens: 56th Terrace - 56th Street
725478f-a.text:
56th Terrace (background), between 56th (left) and 58th Street
(right). Maspeth Ave. (foreground) makes a right angle turn in the
background intersecting with Maurice Ave. and 58th Street. The old
location of the buildings in the background was on the north side of
the Road to Town Landing between Maspeth Creek and Betts Ave. The
Clinton Park Hotel (in center of view) was demolished in September 1929.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
